/* gamedata-w5-slab.mjs — The Slab (Divinity Slab) item-completion registry + getSlabBonus /
 * getSlabBonus_AllMulti formulas, extracted verbatim from N.js (v1.19-era). GENERATED by a
 * one-off extraction script (scratchpad, not committed); refresh after a major patch.
 *
 * WHAT "THE SLAB" IS: a UI panel (World 5 town) that shows every item you have EVER obtained
 * account-wide as a checklist grid, and pays out several small permanent account bonuses that
 * scale with how many distinct items you've found. It is NOT the same system as Sailing
 * Artifacts (whose chest/tier mechanics live in sailing.js/gamedata-cards.mjs) — but 4 of the
 * 8 "Slab" bonus hooks documented below are physically Sailing Artifacts whose formula happens
 * to read the same item-count source.
 *
 * SOURCE TABLE: `na.SlabItemSort=function(){return"Copper Iron Gold Plat ... DungEquipmentRings4".split(" ")}`
 * at N.js:24037 (one giant space-separated string, `.split(" ")`'d into an array). Registered into
 * `CustomLists.h.SlabItemSort` at N.js:30246 (init) and N.js:34309 (reload path).
 *
 * EXACT COUNT: **1911 entries**, verified via a scratch Node script that located the literal
 * source string between the `na.SlabItemSort=function(){return"` marker and the terminating
 * `".split(" ")}` marker (a naive `indexOf('"}')` first pass overshot into unrelated later code
 * and produced a bogus 4842 — the fix was anchoring on the exact `.split(" ")` terminator).
 * All 1911 entries are UNIQUE (no duplicate ids). Cross-checked byte-for-byte (order and content,
 * 0 mismatches) against idleon-toolbox's `data/website-data.json` top-level `"slab"` array, which
 * is also exactly 1911 entries — despite this repo's earlier research note that idleon-toolbox
 * "has no dedicated slab parser"; that's true of a *parser* (no `parsers/world-5/slab.ts`), but
 * the raw table IS present as static extracted data, and (see below) `getSlabBonus` DOES exist
 * as a function in `parsers/world-5/sailing.ts:904`, formula-identical to the N.js one derived
 * independently here.
 *
 * HOW COMPLETION IS ACTUALLY CONSUMED (read at N.js:17503-17511, the Slab UI render block, and
 * N.js:4758/20839-20844, the "Wisdom Card" Caverns minigame):
 *   - Ownership check: `D.contains(Cards[1], SlabItemSort[idx])` — `Cards[1]` (an
 *     `a.engine.getGameAttribute("Cards")[1]` array) is the account-wide list of every distinct
 *     item id ever obtained. Note this is a DIFFERENT "Cards" than the Trading Cards system;
 *     "Cards" here is an overloaded gameAttribute name for the account's all-time item registry.
 *     No exclusion filter is applied at this checklist-render site — it iterates the FULL
 *     1911-entry SlabItemSort array and checks raw ownership. So "Slab completion %" as rendered
 *     to the player = count(SlabItemSort items in Cards[1]) / 1911, unfiltered.
 *   - `Cards[1].length` (total distinct items ever found, NOT filtered to Slab-eligible ones) is
 *     the literal quantity plugged into every getSlabBonus/ArtifactBonus floor() below — i.e. the
 *     bonus formulas use the RAW "items ever found" counter, not a Slab-filtered subset count.
 *   - GREEN CHECKMARK overlay ("GreenSymbol.png", N.js:17509-17510): drawn per-cell when
 *     `D.contains(GreenStacks, SlabItemSort[idx])`. `GreenStacks` is NOT a static na.* table —
 *     it's a live save-state array (`a.engine.getGameAttribute("GreenStacks")`), initialized to
 *     `[]` at new-save creation (N.js:9947), persisted via `addSaveEntryList("GreenStacks",...)`
 *     (N.js:9789) and loaded via `getLoadList("GreenStacks")` gated on save version >=31
 *     (N.js:30148). It's populated by pushing `ChestOrder[f]` item ids on chest-open, deduped
 *     via `D.contains` first (N.js:4659) — i.e. "green stack" = an item you've picked up from a
 *     Loot Pile chest at least once (separate from the Slab's "ever obtained" Cards[1] concept;
 *     an item can be Slab-owned via non-chest means, e.g. crafting, without being green-stacked).
 *     `GreenStacks.length` also feeds a Lab Mainframe bonus directly (N.js:6221,
 *     `LabMFbonuses.h.GrStk = GreenStacks.length`, and node "11"'s bonus =
 *     `LabMFbonuses.h["11"] * GreenStacks.length`) and is rendered as a raw counter at N.js:17111.
 *     The "280" figure from the prior research pass was Dominik's own save's GreenStacks.length —
 *     a live per-save number, not a static constant to hardcode here. There is NO static na.*
 *     "GreenStacks" table to extract; it is 100% save-state, so this file exports none.
 *   - EXCLUSION LIST FOUND (N.js:20839-20841) is scoped to a DIFFERENT feature — the "Wisdom
 *     Card" memory-match minigame in the World-5 Caverns (HoleWisdomCard.png cards), which picks
 *     a random subset of the player's owned-and-Slab-eligible items to use as card faces. It is
 *     NOT applied to the Slab completion checklist itself. Transcribed verbatim — an item is
 *     excluded from the random draw pool if its raw id:
 *       contains "Dust"      contains "Tach"      contains "Island"    contains "Bone"
 *       contains "Genetic"   contains "DungWe"     contains "DungRNG"  contains "Mother"
 *       is exactly "Fish1D"  is exactly "Fish3D"
 *     (plus a same-array-index dedupe check via `D.contains(this._DL1, ...indexOf(...))` so no
 *     item is drawn twice in one minigame session).
 *
 * IN-GAME "COMPLETION" MILESTONES (for context — NOT part of getSlabBonus, but the concrete
 * signal for what a completion ladder should look like on a Slab checklist page):
 *   - Steam/account achievement "Slab_of_Legend" (N.js:24424): "Find a total of {_items in the
 *     Slab" — 10 tiers at [500,600,700,800,900,1000,1100,1200,1300,1405]. Max tier (1405) is only
 *     ~73.5% of the full 1911-item registry — the achievement does not require full completion.
 *   - Weekly Bonus Ballot option (N.js:23796): "Find at least 1850 items, according to The Slab"
 *     -> "+160% Equinox Bar fill rate" (single threshold, no ladder).
 *   - A continuous/steam-style progression entry (N.js:24127): ["Find_at_least_{_items,_as_shown
 *     _by_the_Slab","500","linear","6","1"] — base 500, +6 linear step per following tier (exact
 *     consuming UI not resolved further; out of scope for this extraction).
 *
 * getSlabBonus / getSlabBonus_AllMulti — DISPATCHER: confirmed to be `m._customBlock_Sailing`
 * (the same "d"-string dispatcher that also serves ArtifactBonus, BoatValue, CaptainPedastal*,
 * SailingExpMulti, etc.) — call sites write `m._customBlock_Sailing("SlabboBonus",4,0)` etc.
 * (N.js:17506). There is NO separate `getSlabBonus`-named function in N.js and no case-
 * insensitive "SlabBonus" (no "bo") variant — `grep -i "SlabBonus"` (no "bo") returns zero
 * hits distinct from "SlabboBonus"; the in-client name for this whole feature is "Slabbo".
 *
 * THE 8 HOOKS pushed together into one array at the Slab UI's own bonus-tile row (N.js:17506,
 * `_GenINFO[101]`, rendered as up to 6 populated tiles per N.js:17507's `6>b` loop — 2 of the
 * 8 pushed values are apparently unused/hidden in that particular tile row):
 *   1. Sailing("ArtifactBonus", 2, 0)   -> artifact "Ruble_Cuble"    (Total Dmg)
 *   2. Sailing("ArtifactBonus", 10, 0)  -> artifact "10_AD_Tablet"   (Sailing Speed)
 *   3. Sailing("ArtifactBonus", 18, 0)  -> artifact "Jade_Rock"      (Divinity)
 *   4. Sailing("ArtifactBonus", 20, 0)  -> artifact "Gummy_Orb"      (bits)
 *   5. Sailing("SlabboBonus", 4, 0)     -> Jade Emporium "Jade_Coin_Magnetism" (Jade Coin Gain)
 *   6. Sailing("SlabboBonus", 5, 0)     -> Jade Emporium "Essence_Confetti"    (All Essence Gain)
 *   7. Sailing("SlabboBonus", 6, 0)     -> Superbit 25 "Slabby|Spelunking"     (Total Spelunking POW)
 *   8. Sailing("SlabboBonus", 7, 0)     -> Superbit 34 "Slabby|Research"      (Research EXP gain)
 * (all 8 pushes verbatim at N.js:17506: `this._DL1.push(m._customBlock_Sailing("ArtifactBonus",2,0));
 * this._DL1.push(m._customBlock_Sailing("ArtifactBonus",10,0));this._DL1.push(m._customBlock_Sailing
 * ("ArtifactBonus",18,0));this._DL1.push(m._customBlock_Sailing("ArtifactBonus",20,0));this._DL1.push
 * (m._customBlock_Sailing("SlabboBonus",4,0));this._DL1.push(m._customBlock_Sailing("SlabboBonus",5,0));
 * this._DL1.push(m._customBlock_Sailing("SlabboBonus",6,0));this._DL1.push(m._customBlock_Sailing
 * ("SlabboBonus",7,0));this._GenINFO[101]=this._DL1;`)
 *
 * ArtifactBonus items 1-4 above (l = 2, 10, 18, 20) get their "main bonus" (ArtifactInfo[l][3])
 * scaled by the Slab formula INSIDE the generic ArtifactBonus(-1) recompute loop, N.js:17731-17732
 * (verbatim, `p`=Lab dispatcher, `m`=Sailing dispatcher):
 *   if (l===2 || l===10 || l===18 || l===20 || l===999)  // 999 never actually matches a real idx
 *     SailzArtiBonusL[l] = ArtifactInfo[l][3]
 *       * (1 + MainframeBonus(15)/100)                      // Lab node 15 "Slab_Sovereignty"
 *       * Sailing("SlabboBonus_AllMulti", 0, 0)
 *       * Math.floor(Math.max(0, Cards[1].length - 500) / 10)
 * ArtifactInfo[l][3] base values (parsed from na.ArtifactInfo, N.js:23861-23871): Ruble_Cuble=1,
 * 10_AD_Tablet=4, Jade_Rock=3, Gummy_Orb=15 — i.e. "+1/+4/+3/+15% <stat> per 10 items found after
 * 500", each further scaled by the two multipliers above. Cross-checked EXACTLY against
 * idleon-toolbox's inline artifact-bonus math (parsers/world-5/sailing.ts:773-786): same
 * `Math.floor(Math.max(0, lootedItems - 500) / 10)` term, same 4 artifact names, 0 mismatches.
 *
 * "SlabboBonus_AllMulti" (N.js:17745, verbatim):
 *   (1 + Summoning2("MeritocBonusz", 23, 0) / 100)
 *   * (1 + Thingies("LegendPTS_bonus", 28, 0) / 100)     // Legend Talent "+1 Slab" (2 ranks, cost 15 each)
 *   * (1 + Summoning("VaultUpgBonus", 74, 0) / 100)
 * Cross-checked EXACTLY against idleon-toolbox's `slabMultipliers` (sailing.ts:912-915, which ALSO
 * folds in the Lab node-15 "Slab_Sovereignty" multiplier that N.js keeps as a separate outer
 * factor rather than inside SlabboBonus_AllMulti itself — same net formula, different grouping).
 *
 * "SlabboBonus" (N.js:17745-17747, verbatim; `p`=Lab dispatcher `_customBlock_MainframeBonus`,
 * `m`=Sailing dispatcher, `a.engine.getGameAttribute("Cards")[1].length`=total distinct items
 * ever found account-wide):
 *   b===4 ? (Ninja("EmporiumBonus",17,0)===1
 *              ? 5   * (1+MainframeBonus(15)/100) * SlabboBonus_AllMulti * floor(max(0, len-1000)/10)
 *              : 0)
 *   : b===5 ? (Ninja("EmporiumBonus",18,0)===1
 *              ? 3   * (1+MainframeBonus(15)/100) * SlabboBonus_AllMulti * floor(max(0, len-1000)/10)
 *              : 0)
 *   : b===6 ? (GamingStatType("SuperBitType",25,0)===1
 *              ? 3   * (1+MainframeBonus(15)/100) * SlabboBonus_AllMulti * floor(max(0, len-1300)/5)
 *              : 0)
 *   : b===7 ? (GamingStatType("SuperBitType",34,0)===1
 *              ? 0.1 * (1+MainframeBonus(15)/100) * SlabboBonus_AllMulti * floor(max(0, len-1300)/5)
 *              : 0)
 *   : 0
 * (the dispatcher's final `:1` in the source is `_customBlock_Sailing`'s own default return for
 * an unmatched "d" string — not part of the SlabboBonus b-switch.)
 * Gates: EmporiumBonus 17/18 = Jade Emporium purchases "Jade_Coin_Magnetism" / "Essence_Confetti"
 * (na.JadeUpg idx 17/18); SuperBitType 25/34 = Gaming Superbit unlocks whose na.GamingUpg
 * description text is literally "Adds a new bonus to The Slab: +% Total Spelunking POW" (idx 25)
 * and "...+% Research EXP gain" (idx 34) — the game's own text confirms these ARE "Slab" bonuses,
 * not just formula coincidence. Cross-checked EXACTLY against idleon-toolbox's `getSlabBonus`
 * (parsers/world-5/sailing.ts:904-925) — identical 5/3/3/0.1 multipliers, identical 1000/1300
 * thresholds, identical /10 and /5 divisors, 0 mismatches (toolbox's `lootedItems` = `account.
 * looty.rawLootedItems` = `Cards[1].length`, sourced from `parsers/misc.ts:349`'s `getSlab`, which
 * DOES exist as a full slab-checklist parser feeding `account.looty` — contrary to this repo's
 * prior research note that idleon-toolbox has "no dedicated slab parser"; that note appears to
 * have missed `misc.ts:getSlab` and `world-5/sailing.ts:getSlabBonus`, both present and correct).
 *
 * MainframeBonus(15) is NOT a 9th hook — it's the Lab node 15 "Slab_Sovereignty" multiplier
 * (already documented as `LAB_NODES[15]` in gamedata-lab.mjs, emporium-gated on JadeUpg id 9)
 * that feeds INTO every one of the 8 hooks above as `(1+MainframeBonus(15)/100)`. Its own
 * in-game tooltip (N.js:24023) reads: "'Slab_Sovereignty' gives an additional {%_boost to all
 * Slab Bonuses!" — confirms it's a shared multiplier, not a distinct bonus target.
 * -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- */

